{"name":"Glimpse Destiny","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You peer into one of many contingent futures. Choose an enemy and an ally, both within 30 feet of you, and attempt a Religion check against the enemy's Will DC.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Success</strong> Your ally gains a +5-foot status bonus to their Speed when they @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Bcxarzksqt9ezrs6]{Stride} toward the enemy, and when they @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.UHpkTuCtyaPqiCAB]{Step} toward or around the enemy, they also gain the benefits of @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.other-effects.I9lfZUiCwMiGogVi]{Standard Cover} against the enemy. The enemy becomes the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The enemy becomes the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The enemy's fate is inscrutable to you. They become immune to your @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-actions.2AQichC2pK5tvFcH]{Glimpse Destiny} for 1 hour.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"glimpse-destiny","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_expertise","oracle"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"offensive","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.9p7UxjfBHvTgFgQO"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127185576,"modifiedTime":1686136187249,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"2AQichC2pK5tvFcH"}
{"name":"Patron’s Eye","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You mark a foe to receive your patron's attention. Choose an enemy within 30 feet and attempt a skill check matching your spellcasting tradition against the enemy's Will DC.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> Until the end of your next turn, when the enemy attempts to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.XMcnh4cSI32tljXa]{Hide} or @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Sneak]{Sneak} from you, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.ust1jJSCZQUhBZIz]{Takes Cover} from you, or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Bcxarzksqt9ezrs6]{Strides} away from you, they first become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 1}. They are aware of this effect. They become the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> Until the end of your next turn, when the enemy attempts to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.XMcnh4cSI32tljXa]{Hide} or @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Sneak]{Sneak} from you, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.ust1jJSCZQUhBZIz]{Takes Cover} from you, or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Bcxarzksqt9ezrs6]{Strides} away from you, they become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 1} after completing the action. They are aware of this effect. They become the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The enemy becomes the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The enemy wards themselves against your patron's eye and is immune to your @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-actions.613nTcGCJKBFGxys]{Patron’s Eye} for 1 hour. If they were the target of your expertise, they lose that designation.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"patrons-eye","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_expertise","witch"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"offensive","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.r4BWuVvj5I3LrM6b"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127185576,"modifiedTime":1686136969697,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"613nTcGCJKBFGxys"}
{"name":"Eldritch Favor","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You ask your willing witch ally to beseech their patron on your behalf.</p>\n<p>They use their reaction to grant you a +2 circumstance bonus on checks to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recall Knowledge} and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.BlAOM2X92SI6HMtJ]{Seek} before the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-effects.rcqzNRXsYpu3vSYj]{Effect: Eldritch Favor}</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"eldritch-favor","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_consult","linguistic"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"interaction","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127058088,"modifiedTime":1686137089948,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"6lIcFsiVzizZ6qSP"}
{"name":"Beseech Nature","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You ask your willing druid ally to intercede for you with the nearby wildlife. They use their reaction to grant your next Strike this turn additional slashing damage equal to the number of damage dice.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"beseech-nature","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_consult","linguistic"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"interaction","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127058088,"modifiedTime":1686135536158,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"BPxirIHxxejdjWCP"}
{"name":"Channel Psyche","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You call out to your willing psychic ally to shore up your mental reserves.</p>\n<p>They use their reaction to grant you a +1 circumstance bonus to Will saves until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-effects.zABnPUIg8jmhtAXy]{Effect: Channel Psyche}</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"channel-psyche","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_consult","linguistic"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"interaction","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127058088,"modifiedTime":1686136429277,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"D6h3OAG7aTvtAa8d"}
{"name":"Toppling Spell","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You leverage your willpower against an indomitable foe. If your next action is to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} with the incapacitation trait, choose one creature affected by the spell. You treat this creature as 2 levels lower for the purposes of resolving the incapacitation effect. If this incapacitation spell directly or indirectly causes the encounter to end (as verified by your GM), you regain your use of @UUID[Compendium.world.magic-specializations-actions.EZ4KVsYjRYXxZfSW]{Toppling Spell} for the day.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"toppling-spell","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["concentrate","metamagic"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":null,"actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false,"frequency":{"max":1,"per":"day"}},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.4ifrDw8SpM7lMHhB"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686125602758,"modifiedTime":1686125908029,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"EZ4KVsYjRYXxZfSW"}
{"name":"Divine Rebuke","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You chastise a foe in the name of your deity. Choose a creature within 30 feet and attempt a Religion check against their Will DC. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to this check if they have committed an act anathema to your deity within the past hour.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature takes [[/r @actor.level[mental]]]{mental damage equal to your level} and a -2 circumstance penalty to checks using your deity's divine skill until the end of your next turn. They become the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-effects.GOayi0jEYtUyXcq2]{Effect: Divine Rebuke (Critical)}</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes [[/r (floor((@actor.level)/2))[mental]]]{mental damage equal to half your level} and a -1 circumstance penalty to checks using your deity's divine skill until the end of your next turn. They become the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-effects.XNreLBRuGETkDuzR]{Effect: Divine Rebuke}</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The enemy becomes the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> Your deity withholds their rebuke. The creature is immune to your @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-actions.FWkgcZBTZVsNRfc1]{Divine Rebuke} for 1 hour. If they were the target of your expertise, they lose that designation.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"divine-rebuke","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["cleric","hb_expertise","mental"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"offensive","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.J5SGf5KhW6FDVDPs"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127185576,"modifiedTime":1686135611665,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"FWkgcZBTZVsNRfc1"}
{"name":"Bloodline Ward","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You conjure an avatar of your ancestral lineage that imposes itself upon a foe. The form of this avatar matches a type of creature associated with your bloodline. Choose an enemy within 30 feet and attempt a skill check matching your spellcasting tradition against the enemy's Will DC.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The enemy is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Flat-Footed]{Flat-Footed} against you until the end of your next turn. They become the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The enemy is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.AJh5ex99aV6VTggg]{Flat-Footed} against you until the end of your turn. They become the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The enemy becomes the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The enemy wards themselves against the avatar and is immune to your @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-actions.PtniamYi2JAME8Zw]{Bloodline Ward} for 1 hour. If they were the target of your expertise, they lose that designation.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"bloodline-ward","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_expertise","sorcerer"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"offensive","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rQNR8e43QQ3paVd3"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127185576,"modifiedTime":1686136753797,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"PtniamYi2JAME8Zw"}
{"name":"Invoke Nature’s Fury","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You call animals, plants, and elemental forces in the area to assail a foe. Choose a creature within 30 feet and attempt a Nature check against their Will DC.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature becomes physically hampered as they attack you and your allies. Until the end of their next turn, their multiple attack penalty increases by 1 (a -6 on their second attack roll and - 12 on their third, or -5 and -10 for attacks with the agile trait), and their @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.Tkd8sH4pwFIPzqTr]{Grab}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.BCLvAx4Pz4MLa2pu]{Knockdown}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.t6cx9FOODmeZQNYl]{Push}, and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.3JOi2cMcGhT3eze1]{Rend} actions require 2 actions instead of 1. They become the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature becomes physically hampered as they attack you and your allies. Until the end of their next turn, their multiple attack penalty increases by 1 (a -6 on their second attack roll and -12 on their third, or -5 and -10 for attacks with the agile trait). They become the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The enemy becomes the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> They frighten away the forces of nature and become immune to your @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-actions.RGXTy7hRhipyE5Xw]{Invoke Nature’s Fury} for 1 hour. If they were the target of your expertise, they lose that designation.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"invoke-natures-fury","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["druid","hb_expertise"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"offensive","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iRdM1BmSH2mfeXYz"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127185576,"modifiedTime":1686135600690,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"RGXTy7hRhipyE5Xw"}
{"name":"Combination Cantrip","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You call upon your willing sorcerer ally to empower your weapon. Attempt a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.VjxZFuUXrCU94MWR]{Strike}. On a hit, your sorcerer ally uses their reaction to cast a cantrip in their spell repertoire against the same target. If the cantrip normally targets multiple creatures or an area, it affects only the target, instead. The enemy must be within range as usual. Any damage rolled for the cantrip uses its minimum value.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"combination-cantrip","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_consult","linguistic"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"interaction","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127058088,"modifiedTime":1686136710766,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"Vu1aKhU0MSWcyEp2"}
{"name":"Eat Magic Item","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>You are holding a magic item that isn’t broken and that you’ve Identified. This can’t be an artifact or intelligent item. </p>\n<hr />\n<p>You consume the magic item, destroying it in the process. If the item is consumable, choose a common cantrip of your magic eater tradition; if it’s not consumable, choose a common non-cantrip spell, instead, also from your magic eater tradition, of a level up to half the item’s level rounded up. The spell must require one or two actions to cast, and must share at least one trait with the item. You @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast the Spell} as an innate spell of your chosen tradition, heightened to a spell level equal to half the item’s level rounded up. If the item was cursed or if you critically failed at Identifying the item, instead of casting a spell, you become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeebled 1}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.i3OJZU2nk64Df3xm]{Clumsy 1}, and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.4D2KBtexWXa6oUMR]{Drained 1}. A cursed item is not destroyed in this way.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"eat-magic-item","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["manipulate"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":null,"actions":{"value":2},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxvATLXaF1vCJoWD"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686126121383,"modifiedTime":1686126934273,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"W7om7zFeKkZz9FUv"}
{"name":"Harmonize","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You hum a merry tune as you undertake a task. Your expert bard ally can Aid you using Performance on a skill check you attempt before the end of your turn.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"harmonize","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_consult","linguistic"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"interaction","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Mik4tKvwq8J1WUoo"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127058088,"modifiedTime":1686134316952,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"ZAnw1NTJOmGeHkGL"}
{"name":"Prompt Knowledge","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You request information from your willing wizard ally.</p>\n<p>They use their reaction to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recall Knowledge}.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"prompt-knowledge","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_consult","linguistic"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"interaction","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127058088,"modifiedTime":1686136998788,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"aCyD9duJsErzoyG9"}
{"name":"Call Medic","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>You are within a consultant cleric ally’s reach and they have a free hand.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You request medical support from your willing cleric ally. They use their reaction with the manipulate trait to grant you temporary Hit Points equal to their level. They last 1 minute.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"call-medic","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_consult","healing","linguistic"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"interaction","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127058088,"modifiedTime":1686134439333,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"fLqJl853njDa8AZ5"}
{"name":"Arcane Resonance","type":"action","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You find a resonant frequency of an enemy's life force and temporarily attune your magic to it. Choose an enemy within 30 feet and name a spell that you or an ally knows. Attempt an Arcana check against the target's Will DC.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> Until the end of your next turn, whenever anyone within 30 feet of the enemy casts the chosen spell, the enemy takes force damage equal to the spell's level. They become the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> Until the end of your next turn, whenever you cast the chosen spell within 30 feet of the enemy, they take force damage equal to the spell's level. They become the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The enemy becomes the target of your expertise. Any creature who previously was the target of your expertise loses that designation.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The enemy wards themselves against your efforts. They become immune to your @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-actions.fTRnncaTaynGhKaQ]{Arcane Resonance} for 1 hour. If they were the target of your expertise, they lose that designation.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"arcane-resonance","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["hb_expertise","wizard"]},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"category":"offensive","actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686127185576,"modifiedTime":1686137046926,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":